{"questionId":"9069589","questionHtml":"<p>For the reaction <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>I</mtext></math><sub>2 </sub>(g) + 3Cl<sub>2</sub> (g) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇌</mo></math> 2<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>I</mtext></math>Cl<sub>3</sub> (g) at a certain temperature, the equilibrium&nbsp;concentrations are (in mol dm<sup>−3</sup>):</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">[<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>I</mtext></math><sub>2</sub>] = 0.20, [Cl<sub>2</sub>] = 0.20, [<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>I</mtext></math>Cl<sub>3</sub>] = 2.0</p>\n<p>What is the value of <em>K</em><sub>c</sub>?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp; 0.25</p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;50</p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;2500</p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;5000</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069589","referenceCode":"22N.1.hl.TZ0.22","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"For the reaction I2 (g) + 3Cl2 (g) ⇌ 2ICl3 (g) at a certain temperature, the equilibrium concentrations are (in mol dm−3): [I2] = 0.20, [Cl2] = 0.20, [ICl3] = 2.0 What is the value","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"22","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 17: Equilibrium","17.1 The equilibrium law","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 17: Equilibrium"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}